Yes. Let’s build the abstracted layer above GeoAtlas.

Field Engine

A general engine for reading, modeling, and shaping complex fields

GeoAtlas is one instantiation of it.
The Field Engine is the parent architecture.

Its job is to answer:

What are the entities, relationships, flows, pressures, meanings, and future trajectories in a field—and what actions best fit that field?

This is the generalized machine for:
	•	markets
	•	cities
	•	culture
	•	logistics
	•	organizations
	•	portfolios
	•	ecosystems
	•	memetic space
	•	personal decision environments

