5. The engine loop

This is the full operational cycle:

Step 1 — Observe

Take in raw events, measurements, text, maps, transactions, reviews, org charts, logistics traces, whatever fits the domain.

Step 2 — Normalize

Convert everything into the shared ontology:
	•	nodes
	•	edges
	•	flows
	•	field states
	•	timestamps

Step 3 — Build state

Assemble a current field snapshot.

Step 4 — Infer hidden structure

Estimate:
	•	clusters
	•	bottlenecks
	•	attractor basins
	•	weak ties
	•	white space
	•	contagion paths
	•	overload points

Step 5 — Generate interventions

Create candidate actions:
	•	place here
	•	move this
	•	bridge these
	•	slow that
	•	bundle these
	•	split this segment
	•	add redundancy
	•	sequence rollout differently

Step 6 — Simulate

Run counterfactuals and perturbation tests.

Step 7 — Rank

Score interventions by:
	•	field fit
	•	coordination gain
	•	resilience gain
	•	expected return
	•	uncertainty
	•	downside risk

Step 8 — Explain

Return both structured outputs and human-readable reasons.

