8. Domain adapters

The Field Engine becomes useful by plugging in domain adapters.

A. GeoAtlas adapter

Maps:
	•	nodes = places/sites/buildings
	•	flows = people/spend/traffic
	•	fields = demand, rent, sentiment

B. Memetic adapter

Maps:
	•	nodes = memes, topics, creators, communities
	•	flows = attention, reposts, adoption
	•	fields = prestige, hostility, curiosity, fatigue

C. Logistics adapter

Maps:
	•	nodes = warehouses, hubs, stores, trucks
	•	flows = goods, time, capacity
	•	fields = demand pressure, delay risk, weather

D. Organization adapter

Maps:
	•	nodes = teams, people, projects
	•	flows = information, decisions, resources
	•	fields = trust, friction, status, overload

E. Portfolio adapter

Maps:
	•	nodes = assets, bets, sectors
	•	flows = capital, volatility, narrative
	•	fields = macro pressure, liquidity, momentum

Each domain shares the same engine and just swaps meanings.

