14. Guardrails

Because this engine could become manipulative or extractive if built badly, its governance layer should enforce:

Hard rules
	•	no protected-attribute targeting
	•	no coercive optimization
	•	no hidden risk suppression
	•	no invented certainty

Soft rules
	•	surface uncertainty
	•	expose top drivers
	•	keep human override
	•	log major recommendations and changes

Required distinctions

Always separate:
	•	observed signal
	•	inferred structure
	•	predicted outcome
	•	recommended action

That prevents narrative blur.

